Always love is a choice.

232
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:41,490
She says,

233
00:19:41,590 --> 00:19:44,750
You come up against scores of opportunities every day

234
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,670
to love or not to love.

235
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:51,270
You encounter hundreds of small chances

236
00:19:51,270 --> 00:19:52,670
to please your friends,

237
00:19:53,590 --> 00:19:54,470
delight your Lord,

238
00:19:55,150 --> 00:19:56,250
and encourage your family.

239
00:19:57,100 --> 00:20:00,160
That's why love and obedience are intimately linked.

240
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:03,220
You can't have one without the other.

241
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:05,850
It's true, isn't it?

242
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:11,670
Here are some practical ideas about whom and how to love.

243
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:15,800
The first one is probably the easiest.

244
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,180
It's to love those who are close to us.

245
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:22,150
Someone once said,

246
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:25,110
To love the whole world for me is no chore.

247
00:20:26,070 --> 00:20:28,670
The only real problem is my neighbor next door.

248
00:20:30,420 --> 00:20:31,200
It's true, isn't it?

249
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:35,580
Can we love those close to us, close in proximity?

250
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:41,400
Can we demonstrate love to those who are right in our sphere of influence?

251
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:48,740
you know we're commanded to love no matter how inconsiderate our spouse might be at times

252
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:56,300
no matter how unreasonable our parents are no matter how disrespectful our children might be

253
00:20:56,300 --> 00:21:03,800
no matter how selfish our friends are we are to love and display love and peace and patience and

254
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:09,400
kindness to those right around us because the spirit of god is cultivating love in our lives

255
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:15,600
if you want to know if there's love flowing in your home ask these questions

256
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:19,730
H.B. London said, one criteria of family health is this.

257
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:21,510
Are you saying, I'm sorry?

258
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,500
Are you saying, I forgive you?

259
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:33,760
And are you saying, I love you, often, to those in your family, in your immediate sphere?

260
00:21:37,660 --> 00:21:39,440
Criterion for family health, challenging.

261
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:45,660
We're also called to love those who are different from us.

262
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,740
I don't like that person's piercings.

263
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,780
I don't like the color of their skin.

264
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:58,380
and I don't feel comfortable around this person or that person

265
00:21:58,380 --> 00:22:01,140
might be the echo of your heart.

266
00:22:03,180 --> 00:22:06,310
They might be different, but God loves them.

267
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:11,020
They may listen to different music.

268
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:12,520
They may dance to a different beat.

269
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:14,600
They might live in a different neighborhood.

270
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:17,180
They might be a totally different kind of person

271
00:22:17,180 --> 00:22:19,180
with different values and interests,

272
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:23,540
but can we not demonstrate the fruit of the Spirit

273
00:22:23,540 --> 00:22:27,320
in loving others who are different from us?

274
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:34,140
If you keep your eyes open, they will cross your path all the time.

275
00:22:35,430 --> 00:22:38,930
You don't have to go looking very far to find people who are different from us.

276
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:41,630
Just look around this room.

277
00:22:44,090 --> 00:22:46,330
Many of you are very different, and that's great.

278
00:22:47,260 --> 00:22:49,160
That's what heaven will look like one day.

279
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:53,160
The Bible says all nations, all tribes, all languages, all colors

280
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:55,900
will all be at the seat of the throne.

281
00:22:59,250 --> 00:23:01,490
Number three, can we love those who disagree with us?

282
00:23:03,890 --> 00:23:06,090
It's easy to love those who think like we do.

283
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:11,330
Can you love somebody and be gracious and loving

284
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:14,590
and want the best for them even if they disagree?

285
00:23:16,540 --> 00:23:17,960
Remember, friends, that Christians,

286
00:23:18,180 --> 00:23:20,080
even though we disagree within the church,

287
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,260
Christians are never our enemies.

288
00:23:22,540 --> 00:23:23,640
They are our family.

289
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,360
We can love those who disagree with us.

290
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:30,760
We can also finally love those who irritate us.

291
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:32,960
That's a toughie, isn't it?

292
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:35,840
It's hard to love people who bug us.

293
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:44,400
it's not easy to love people who we think are stupid is it or dumb or whatever because they

294
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:50,320
don't think like we do that they bug us they get under our skin oh i wish i wouldn't have to see

295
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:57,420
them every week kind of people you know god can do a lot in your life by growing fruit of the spirit

296
00:23:57,420 --> 00:24:06,300
by just putting them in your path and challenging you to love them as god loves them for somebody

297
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:11,240
in the church that rubs you the wrong way we need to make a special effort change our attitude and

298
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:20,500
treat others in a loving way by the power of the spirit of God D.L. Moody the great evangelist

299
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:31,010
years ago said this he said joy is love exalted and peace is love and repose long suffering is

300
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:42,490
love enduring. Gentleness is love in society. Goodness is love in action. Faith is love on the

301
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:52,100
battlefield. Meekness is love in school. And temperance is love in training. It's the fruit

302
00:24:52,100 --> 00:25:05,480
of the Spirit as we see how love permeates all of those. Ephesians chapter 5. Follow God's example

303
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:07,100
in everything you do

304
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:10,500
because you are his dear children.

305
00:25:12,130 --> 00:25:14,210
Live a life filled with love for others,

306
00:25:14,690 --> 00:25:16,510
following the example of Christ

307
00:25:16,510 --> 00:25:18,830
who loved you and gave himself

308
00:25:18,830 --> 00:25:21,990
as a sacrifice to take away your sins.

309
00:25:27,190 --> 00:25:28,230
Last week was joy.

310
00:25:29,310 --> 00:25:31,170
This week is love.

311
00:25:32,590 --> 00:25:34,610
Two qualities for a victorious life.

312
00:25:35,090 --> 00:25:37,010
If we live agape love,

313
00:25:38,090 --> 00:25:39,830
love by the power of the Spirit,

314
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:42,330
our lives will be transformed.

315
00:25:42,990 --> 00:25:44,290
We'll have incredible meaning

316
00:25:44,290 --> 00:25:46,690
and we'll be a blessing to many

317
00:25:46,690 --> 00:25:49,070
as we let that cultivate in our soul.

318
00:25:50,990 --> 00:25:52,150
And as it relates to worship,

319
00:25:52,310 --> 00:25:53,270
I conclude with this.

320
00:25:53,390 --> 00:25:57,970
1 Timothy 1, verse 3-5.

321
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:00,760
Paul writes to Timothy,

322
00:26:00,860 --> 00:26:02,280
When I left for Macedonia,

323
00:26:03,420 --> 00:26:05,340
I urged you to stay there in Ephesus

324
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:07,600
and stop those who are teaching wrong doctrine.

325
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,000
Don't let people waste time

326
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,800
in endless speculation over myths

327
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:12,980
and spiritual pedigrees.

328
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:15,440
For these things only cause arguments.

329
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:18,720
They didn't help people live a life of faith in God.

330
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:24,460
The purpose of my instruction is that all the Christians there would be filled with love

331
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:31,080
that comes from a pure heart, a clear conscience, and a sincere faith.

332
00:26:34,540 --> 00:26:39,110
A pure heart, a clear conscience, a sincere faith.

333
00:26:39,510 --> 00:26:45,120
It's my prayer that we of Fullerton First Baptist would be a people that seek the Spirit

334
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:49,340
to cultivate love that comes as we generate from God

335
00:26:49,340 --> 00:26:54,200
a pure heart, a clear conscience, and sincere faith.

336
00:26:56,870 --> 00:26:59,210
And the neat thing is when we live out those values,

337
00:26:59,330 --> 00:27:00,850
when we live out those experiences,

338
00:27:00,970 --> 00:27:03,970
when we allow God to stretch us to love others

339
00:27:03,970 --> 00:27:06,530
who are like us and different from us,

340
00:27:07,010 --> 00:27:09,210
who irritate us, who are close to us,

341
00:27:09,470 --> 00:27:12,090
whatever we do, whoever we love,

342
00:27:12,980 --> 00:27:14,900
that we would then bring that love

343
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:17,350
into this worship center

344
00:27:17,350 --> 00:27:22,950
That we bring it in as the culmination of our worship with God all week

345
00:27:22,950 --> 00:27:29,450
as we now come and bring and celebrate the love that God has filled our lives with throughout the week.

346
00:27:29,670 --> 00:27:32,310
The victories we've had as we've loved somebody difficult.

347
00:27:33,980 --> 00:27:36,440
The victory that we loved somebody who was different.

348
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:40,790
And we offer that in worship to God.

349
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:48,640
As I said last week, we bring those victorious qualities into the sanctuary week after week.

350
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:51,080
and we offer that to God

351
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:54,190
we lift the lid of this place

352
00:27:54,190 --> 00:27:55,610
right off the foundation

353
00:27:55,610 --> 00:27:58,710
we become a real blessing to God

354
00:27:58,710 --> 00:28:02,600
and a wonderful place to be as well

355
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:05,690
and may God bless you

356
00:28:05,690 --> 00:28:07,840
as we learn to live

357
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:08,940
agape love

358
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:12,220
as we struggle to be obedient to love

359
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,580
as Jesus loves us

360
00:28:13,580 --> 00:28:17,840
as we surrender our wills to the Spirit

361
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:19,340
that each day we say

362
00:28:19,340 --> 00:28:21,640
Lord may I love those around me

363
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,840
and those you bring into my path

364
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:24,800
may I be faithful

365
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:29,010
in living as you've loved me.

366
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:30,880
Would you pray with me?

367
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:33,250
Gracious Lord,

368
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:36,640
you have so much love for us,

369
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:37,260
it's overwhelming.

370
00:28:38,460 --> 00:28:40,100
So much love that came

371
00:28:40,100 --> 00:28:42,360
literally in the form of your son

372
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:44,020
coming to earth and living a life

373
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,080
and dying for us.

374
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:48,660
And Lord, that's just amazing.

375
00:28:51,780 --> 00:28:52,920
And Father, I pray now

376
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:54,580
that because of your love for us,

377
00:28:55,590 --> 00:28:56,770
because of your spirit

378
00:28:56,770 --> 00:28:59,110
that's come upon our lives,

379
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:02,230
we'd open ourselves more to him.

380
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:06,320
We stay more in tune, more in step with the Spirit.

381
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:09,600
That we listen to the small voice of your Spirit speaking,

382
00:29:10,730 --> 00:29:11,650
love that person.

383
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:13,930
And here's how.

384
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:19,480
Father, we're praying that as we live out these values,

385
00:29:21,060 --> 00:29:24,030
as we live out joy and love,

386
00:29:25,050 --> 00:29:27,690
that we would bring them in a powerful way for worship,

387
00:29:28,570 --> 00:29:29,790
that you would be blessed.

388
00:29:30,330 --> 00:29:34,350
And I pray you'd raise the watermark of love in this church,

389
00:29:35,860 --> 00:29:38,200
that our guests would know that you are here,

390
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:39,560
because we love.

391
00:29:41,660 --> 00:29:43,760
And Father, I pray that you'd bless each of us

392
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,100
as we attempt to love those

393
00:29:45,100 --> 00:29:47,240
who are different and difficult.

394
00:29:48,610 --> 00:29:49,690
Those are hard things, Lord.

395
00:29:51,660 --> 00:29:53,540
But I pray we'd be open and successful

396
00:29:53,540 --> 00:29:56,560
because we follow and we trust you.

397
00:29:59,650 --> 00:30:00,910
So Lord, as that hymn says,

398
00:30:01,010 --> 00:30:02,390
lay some soul upon our heart

399
00:30:02,390 --> 00:30:03,570
that we might love them today.

400
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:08,220
And may we be victorious in that experience

401
00:30:08,220 --> 00:30:11,890
because you're doing it through us.

402
00:30:15,970 --> 00:30:17,030
Expand our hearts.

403
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:19,720
Expand our actions of love

404
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:23,240
and have your way with us.

405
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:25,580
We're yours, Lord.

406
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,260
We want to be obedient

407
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:29,860
and be your children filled with love.

408
00:30:31,220 --> 00:30:32,820
We pray these things in Jesus' name.

409
00:30:33,840 --> 00:30:34,100
Amen.

